title: USF rallies to move to 8-0
text:
USF rallies to move to 8-0 
By Dean Pantazi - 21 Alive October 24, 2015 Updated Oct 24, 2015 at 11:35 PM EDT 
ARLINGTON, HEIGHTS, Ill. (21 Alive - Nick Ferrer fired two touchdown passes and Spencer Cowherd and Na'Shawn Lewis returned interceptions for score to propel seventh ranked Saint Francis to a 39-28 win over No. 9 Robert Morris on Saturday. 
Justin Green was the star of the running game with 140 yards on 19 carries, including a 42 yard touchdown run. 
Seth Coate had another big receiving day with five catches for 142 yards and a touchdown. 
The Cougars moved to 8-0 and further enhanced their playoff position.
